KW  - Factor price equalization
KW  - Integrated world economy
KW  - Lens condition
AB  - Deardorff (1994)provides a condition that is necessary for factor price equalization across countries. This is a generalization of the condition that “country endowments should lie in the diversification cone” from the standard 2×2×2 Heckscher–Ohlin model to the case of many goods, countries and factors. He also shows that this condition is sufficient in the case of two countries and conjectures that the sufficiency might hold in general. In this paper we establish the sufficiency in further cases. However, we show by a counterexample that the sufficiency does not hold in general.
